The paper discusses the issue of unintentional discrimination in machine learning algorithms and proposes the need for developing theoretical understanding and fundamental principles for prevention. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the need for accountability and potential regulations against machine learning, which could fall under the sub-categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of analyzing the machine learning process as a whole, which could also relate to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
